node.text:
This is the “Half Rabbit” statue in Vila Nova de Gaia, Portugal. Bordallo II made it entirely out of trash to protest human wastefulness and unsustainable consumerism. I love how half of the rabbit is painted and the other half was left bare. What pieces of trash can you spot in this sculpture? I see a lot of street signs! #streetart #portugal #gaia #vilanovadegaia 

The other videos are from my port wine tour in Gaia…just to show the amazing architecture and views😋

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. in Paradise. May be an image of brick wall and text that says 'ILICKEDIT SO IT'S MINE'.
Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. on July 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, bridge and monument.

node.text:
An afternoon in New York City✨ 
We didn’t know what to do for the day, so we randomly hopped on the IKEA ferry and rode over to Brooklyn. The line for the ferry heading back to the city was endless, so we decided to walk over the Brooklyn Bridge to get back, instead—and, the views were amazing😍 Although, I have to say, be careful on the bridge; I nearly got run over by 6-7 bicycles…it was just like being in Amsterdam🤣 Have you ever walked across this bridge? #brooklyn #brooklynbridge #newyorknewyork

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. on July 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Such a great day in Miami with friends! This little island is the perfect starting point for a #jetski excursion😍 I’ve been riding jet skis since I was 9, so I am a wild animal out on the water😝 You never want to be sitting behind me when I’m driving one…unless you’re in the mood for a swim🤣 
.
.
.
#jetskiing #miamibeach #florida #summer

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. in Cape Cod, Massachussets with @bayanjaber92, and @firangizzasadova. May be an image of 1 person, dog and outdoors.

node.text:
Summers in Cape Cod are so much fun! It was great to be able to take day trips here when I was (briefly—thanks, covid) going to med school in Boston! 

Missing this fabulous beach day with @bayanjaber92 and @firangizzasadova❤️❤️ 

I will say it’s an impossible place to be a vegan or vegetarian, though—pack your own lunch, if you are! Everything is seafood🙈

#capecod #summers #girlstrip #boston

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. in Virginia Beach, Virginia with @1blondefish. May be an image of 1 person and body of water.

node.text: Nothing beats a Virginia summer! I love the country-beachy vibes here in Virginia Beach! Plus, there’s nothing better than catching up with friends! @1blondefish and I met in middle school, were roommates in college, lived together in LA, and are still besties after more than twenty years! #virginiabeach #summer #bffs #beachlife

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. in Porto, Portugal with @visitportugal, and @visitporto. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: I had such a fun time on Vila Nova de Gaia’s port wine tour! We went to three different cellars and tasted SEVEN different ports😅 Luckily, our whole tour group was vegan/vegetarian (soo surprising—especially in Europe!), so we went out for vegan food afterwards to soak up all that wine🍷 Group tours are a great way to make friends when you travel. Just don’t make my mistake—definitely eat lunch before you go! Otherwise, you’ll have a solid buzz by the end of the first hour (the tour takes four hours!)!🤪 #porto #portugal #portwine #vegan #winetasting

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Kennedy Summers, M.D. on June 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text: How beautiful (and chilly!🥶) is #Porto?😍 These blue tiles on the building behind me are called azulejos, and they are quintessential Portugal! Swipe right to see some incredible architecture🤩🤩 #portugal #azulejos #oporto #amazingarchitecture

node.text: These views in #Portugal wouldn’t seem out of place in the Caribbean😍 I can’t believe how gorgeous the #AtlanticOcean is out here! The water is most definitely is not this clean or this blue in Virginia! There are also tons of cool caves to explore! I’ll post those pics soon😊 Would you visit here? #setubal #arrabida #viewsfordays

node.text: I loved exploring this field in #Setubal!🌾 Well, actually...this is where our RV broke down (yay #vanlife), so @marco_woe (📸) and I took advantage of the situation and squeezed in a quick #photoshoot while we waited for the tow truck! How amazing is this sky?😍😍 I really love being in nature! Are you more of a country person or a city person?
